e announcement via his Twitter handle. Lagos State Government also announced on Monday that five patients who recovered from the COVID-19 disease have been discharged. A woman, Oluwaseun Ayodeji Osowobi, who was among the discharged, recounted her experience in isolation centre while battling with coronavirus in Nigeria. “I thought I was going to die & contemplated a succession plan for @StandtoEndRape. I was on drugs daily. Sometimes, I‘d take 8 tablets in the morning, 13 tablets in the afternoon, 10 at night. My system threw everything out! Water, food, soap & all disgusted me. But I’d look at the wall & force myself to stay hydrated — drank ORS. I FOUGHT TO LIVE! I FOUGHT!!” Vanguard News Nigeria. By Rasheed Sobowale The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) Saturday confirmed 4 new coronavirus cases in Oyo State bringing the total in the state to seven (7). This was contained in the Centre's report of eight (8) new confirmed coronavirus cases in Nigeria, as total cases rise from 89… March 29, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" Coronavirus crisis in Nigeria escalated yesterday as the number of cases hit 89. The figure of infections was 81 as of Friday night March 29, 2020 In "Health" By James Ogunnaike - Abeokuta Ogun State Governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun has announced that the total lockdown of the state which was scheduled to commence today (Monday by 11pm) has been shifted till Friday this week. The shift in date for the lockdown, according to the Ogun State governor would enable both… March 30, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"